titleInfo.title: Photomontage of young men at camp, men in front of the Parthanon, a 4-H Club member, nature pictures, an athlete and his coach, the Banner composition room and two ads. Nashville Banner, 1931 October 18.

mods.abstract: Photomontage of young men at Vanderbilt University's Y. M. C. A. camp, Floridians planning their state's exhibit at Nashville's World Fair, a 4-H Club contest winner, a chestnut burr, a silhouetted tree, a football player and his coach, the Banner composition room, and two ads. 16 x 21.5 in. Forms part of the Nashville Newspaper Rotogravure Digital Images Collection.

originInfo.publisher: Metropolitan Nashville/Davidson County Archives, Nashville Public Library
